---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy â€” DotEdit">
  <main id="main-content" class="py-32 px-6">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] prose-legal">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] hover:text-[var(--color-text)] transition-colors duration-200 mb-10"
      >
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M19 12H5"/><polyline points="12 19 5 12 12 5"/>
        </svg>
        Back to home
      </a>

      <h1 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-[28px] md:text-[36px] leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.02em] mb-2">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-10">
        Last updated: February 2026
      </p>

      <section class="space-y-6 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-2">Summary</h2>
          <p>
            DotEdit does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. The app runs entirely on your Mac with no network calls, no analytics, and no telemetry.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-2">Data Collection</h2>
          <p>DotEdit collects <strong>no data whatsoever</strong>. Specifically:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>No personal information</li>
            <li>No usage analytics or telemetry</li>
            <li>No crash reports</li>
            <li>No cookies or tracking</li>
            <li>No network requests of any kind</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-2">File Access</h2>
          <p>
            DotEdit reads and writes <code class="text-sm font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] bg-[var(--color-surface)] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">.env</code> files that you explicitly open. Files are processed locally in memory and are never transmitted anywhere. The app runs inside the macOS App Sandbox.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-2">Local Storage</h2>
          <p>
            User preferences (theme, font size, diff mode) are stored locally via macOS UserDefaults. Recent file paths are stored locally for convenience. No data leaves your machine.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-2">Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>None. DotEdit has zero third-party dependencies and makes no external connections.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-2">Website</h2>
          <p>
            This website (<a href="https://dotedit.app" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline">dotedit.app</a>) is a static site. It uses Google Fonts loaded from Google's CDN. No cookies, no analytics, no tracking scripts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-2">Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about this policy? Open an issue on <a href="https://github.com/carlos-andres/DotEdit" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
